1366A - Shovels and Swords
There are three constraints on the number of emeralds:
the number of emeralds can't be greater than $$$a$$$;
the number of emeralds can't be greater than $$$b$$$;
the number of emeralds can't be greater than $$$\frac{a+b}{3}$$$.
So the answer is $$$\min(a, b, \frac{a+b}{3})$$$.
